South Africa's COVID-19 cases has risen to 709. Dr Zweli Mkhize joins Dan Moyane in the studio. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has climbed to 709. The number is a rise of 155 cases from Tuesday's tally of 554. South Africa will go into lockdown for 21 days from Thursday evening in a bid to curb the increase in coronavirus cases.   